---
import BlogLayout from "../layouts/BlogLayout.astro";
---

<BlogLayout title="Sobre / About">

  <!-- PT-BR -->
  <div data-pt>
    <h1>Sobre</h1>

    <p>
    Ola. Eu sou uma pessoa que existe na internet faz um tempo, faco de tudo um pouco e agora veio uma idea de ter um blog.
    </p>

    <p>
    Esse blog e mais pra descrever e deixar escrito o que eu gosto de fazer por ai e ecrever algumas coisas tectnicas para nao esquecer
    </p>

    <h2>Este site</h2>
    <p>
      Feito com <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>.
      Sem rastreamento, sem analytics, sem cookies, sem pop-ups...por enquanto
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: 2em; opacity: 0.5; font-size: 0.85em;">
      <em>
        Esta pagina foi atualizada pela ultima vez quando me lembrei que ela existia.
        As informacoes aqui podem ser imprecisas, desatualizadas ou aspiracionais.
      </em>
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- EN -->
  <div data-en>
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      Hello. I am a person who exists on the internet, which already puts me in a very specific demographic.
    </p>

    <p>
      I write about things I find interesting, mostly because I have nowhere else to put these thoughts
      and my friends have started muting my messages. The topics vary, but the common thread is that
      I got very into something, spent too long in documentation pages, and now feel the compulsive need
      to share what I learned.
    </p>

    <p>
      Professionally, I do things with computers. Specifically the kind that make non-technical people
      nod slowly and change the subject at parties.
    </p>

    <h2>Things I am Currently Obsessed With</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Nix. All of Nix. Nix forever.</li>
      <li>Making my terminal look good in screenshots nobody asked to see</li>
      <li>The philosophical implications of declarative systems (see: Nix)</li>
      <li>Finding the perfect monospace font (current winner: DaddyTimeMono, obviously)</li>
      <li>Blaming systemd for things that are probably my fault</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Things I Have Strong Opinions About</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>SSH keys over passwords. Always. No exceptions. I will die on this hill.</li>
      <li>Tabs vs. spaces: the correct answer is whatever your project already uses. Stop.</li>
      <li>The best backup strategy is the one you actually have vs. the one you planned to set up "this weekend"</li>
      <li>Light mode is for people who enjoy suffering and PDFs</li>
      <li>Dark mode is for people who enjoy suffering and eye strain after age 35</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>This Site</h2>
    <p>
      Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>.
      No tracking, no analytics, no cookies, no pop-ups asking about cookies.
      Just HTML and a monospace font making everything look like I know what I am doing.
    </p>

    <p>
      If something is broken, that is a known issue under active non-investigation.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      I have an email address. If you know me, you know it.
      If you do not, you can find it eventually and I will respond within a timeframe best described as "geological".
    </p>

    <p style="margin-top: 2em; opacity: 0.5; font-size: 0.85em;">
      <em>
        This page was last updated whenever I remembered it existed.
        The information here may be inaccurate, outdated, or aspirational.
      </em>
    </p>
  </div>

</BlogLayout>
